“Life has a funny way of redirecting us towards our true calling. Two bullets may have shattered my hoop dreams, but they ignited a fire within me to fight for those who’ve been wronged.”

“Life is unpredictable, and sometimes it takes a tragedy to show us our true purpose. Two bullets may have taken away my love for basketball, but they gave me a new passion for helping victims of crime.” #survivorsspeak

Opening our extraordinary lineup is a Fire Side Chat featuring @aswad_thomas VP of @safeandjustusa, the largest system reform organizationI the country. As the first disruptor lighting up our stage, Aswad brings with him the spirit of resilience, determination, and a relentless drive for social justice.

Imagine a world where we utilize the prowess of tech and data to reduce the chains of mass incarceration, heal deep-seated traumas, and reclaim countless lives. 💡💻

This isn't just disruption. It's a revolution.

#MidwestCon2023 is more than a conference. It's a call-to-arms for every coder, innovator, and social warrior. It's an opportunity to stand at the forefront of tech-driven social change, a chance to rewrite narratives and redefine futures.

Be a part of this seismic shift. Bring your passion, your ideas, your drive for change. Let's unite in our mission to harness the power of technology for a just, compassionate, and inclusive world.

Don't miss your chance to be part of this transformative event. Reserve your spot NOW. The stage is set. The fire is lit. Will you step into the light? #midwestcon2023 (Link in Bio)

The world is like a mirror. It reflects on whatever you do in it. If you face it smiling, it will smile right back at you. #accra #accraghana🇬🇭 #dettydecember #blackstar

Today, I had the incredible privilege of visiting Elmina Castle and Cape Coast in Ghana, a journey that will forever change me. As a black man, standing here in the castle at the point of return I felt a mix of emotions. I felt anger, grief, sadness and a deep sense of resilience passing through my soul. 

I stood in the same cells and dungeons that held our ancestors captive, forced into the horrific slave trade. Everyday being torn away from their homes, families, culture and their own identities. 

My heart is broken imagining all of our ancestors suffering. Words can’t really describe the deep suffering and loss that has been inflicted against Africans. 

In the midst of my pain, I found a sense of peace in the knowledge that our ancestors never surrendered their spirits and love for each other. That spirit and love for people is deeply rooted inside of me and everything that I do. Now I truly understand why my mother named me Aswad. Now I got to get rid of the Thomas slave name lol

On a serious note, I encourage all of my Africans with roots connected to West Africa to visit Cape Coast and witness this transformative journey for yourselves. 

Africa is in me 🇳🇬 🇹🇬 🇧🇯 🇨🇲 🇬🇭 

Aswad Gyasi (yes that’s my middle name lol) #accra #accraghana🇬🇭 #capecoast #elminacastle #dettydecember #africa #ghana #slavery #yearofthereturn #explorepage #experienceghana
